That camel your soul rented from a barn, you might as well get on good terms
 with it, seeing you are out in the wilderness, traveling.
Sometimes I become my own pulse ... enter that world inside. There I have
 stayed a night marveling at the firmament. Yes, inside any living thing
 are stars.
All that the eye sees is just practice for perfecting ... the inner vision.
I canâ€™t speak anymore of poverty of heart or purse. For wherever I now
 stand a gold mine appears.
How did things change for me, so much for the better? I held God to His word
 when He said, Seek and you will ...
You say that last word for me. You must know that famous phrase. Believe it,
 dear, for it is so very true.
